RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 1 1M All Weather Track CR: 82. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE OCTOBER 15 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 123 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000 (Claiming And Starter Races For $3,500 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHERILINDA broke alertly, conceded the early lead and prompted the modest pace, advanced into the far turn and pressed LYINATTHEBAR to the quarter marker, battled with that rival into the stretch, took command into the final sixteenth and edged away late to prove best. LYINATTHEBAR assumed command away from the start, set a modest pace while prompted through the backstretch run, was pressed into the far turn by SHERILINDA, battled with that rival into the stretch, was outfinished in the final sixteenth and was clear in the end for second. SPLICER tracked the modest pace from the inside, gained ground into the far turn, lacked a final response in the stretch and held well for third. LUCY L bobbled at the start and was away a step slowly, settled outside of runners into the first turn and tracked the modest pace three wide into the backstretch run, was coaxed along two wide into the far turn, raced in traffic and waited for racing room nearing the top of the lane, angled three wide for the drive, could not muster the needed late response and was outfinished for third. ALESHA allowed to settle, saved all of the ground to the far turn, mounted an inside bid in the stretch, could not sustain that run in the late stages and flattened out. ST HELENA tracked the modest pace three wide, was asked for run nearing the quarter marker, lacked a response into the stretch and weakened.

ENTRY.NAME: Sherilinda
ENTRY.COMMENT: off well,prompted pace 2wd,battled stretch,proved best,edged away

ENTRY.NAME: Splicer
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked inside,gain 1/4,no final kick stretch,held well for 3rd

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 2 1M All Weather Track CR: 82. Claiming Purse 13000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 123 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $3,200 (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $2,500 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: COOPERKLIMT crowded at the start by a neighboring rival and was away a bit slowly, tracked the modest pace from the inside, saved all of the ground to the far turn, tipped two wide into the stretch, made a mild gain at the furlong marker, responded into the final sixteenth, closed determinedly and overtook the runner-up in deep stretch to prevail. EFFECTIVE GIG sent away from the start and assumed command in the early going, set modest fractions while well rated through the backstretch run and showed the way to the quarter pole, raced in hand into the lane and extended the lead at mid-stretch, felt pressure from COOPERKLIMT in the final sixteenth, could not hold off the winner and was outfinished, while clear of the rest for second. MY DAD IS THIRSTY crowded COOPERKLIMT leaving the break but was away in good order, took back off of the early pace and stalked into the first turn, stalked the modest pace through the backstretch run, mounted a two wide bid at the quarter marker, lost position into the stretch, was outkicked in the final sixteenth and was clear in the end for third. SHERM allowed to settle while never far back, mounted a two wide bid into the far turn, could not sustain that run into the stretch and flattened out. UNUSUAL CODE tracked the early pace two wide and between runners, improved position into the backstretch run and continued his advance three wide heading to the quarter marker, could not keep pace into the stretch and weakened. FANTASTIC DREAM allowed to settle and raced three wide into the first turn, maintained an outside path through the backstretch run and improved position at the half-mile marker, raced four wide to the quarter pole, dropped back into the stretch and tired in the final furlong.

ENTRY.NAME: Effective Gig
ENTRY.COMMENT: sent,set modest pace,well rated,pressured late,outfinished,2d bst

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 3 6F All Weather Track CR: 80. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE OCTOBER 15 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 123 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000 (Claiming And Starter Races For $3,500 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHEMAKESCENTS away in good order, ceded the early lead and stalked the quick pace outside of runners, gained ground three wide along the turn, vied for the lead into upper stretch and took command at the furlong marker, responded to urging into the final sixteenth and kicked clear to prevail. MISS SKI forwardly placed in the early stages, tracked the fast pace from the inside then chased from the rail into the turn, tipped to the two path in upper stretch, rallied approaching the furlong grounds, could not impact the winner in deep stretch and held well for second. RUNNING LUCK took back off of the fast early pace and tracked from the second flight, maintained an outside path into the turn and raced three then four wide to the quarter marker, rallied at mid-stretch, needed more in the final sixteenth and was clear in the end for third. JASMINE CHIEFTAIN allowed to settle away from the start, tracked two wide into the turn then chased the quick pace to the quarter marker, slipped to the inside into upper stretch and advanced at the furlong marker, needed more in the final sixteenth and offered a mild late rally. ALL prominent early, tracked the fast pace while close up into the turn, slipped to the rail nearing the quarter marker and vied for the lead into the stretch, could not keep pace with SHEMAKESCENTS inside of the furlong marker and weakened in the final stages. NOMI LACKEE bobbled then hit the gate leaving the start and was away a bit slowly, lacked early speed and saved ground while trailing into the turn, chased into the stretch and did not factor. SHELBY GOLD chased the fast early pace while between runners, raced two wide into the turn, chased three wide into the stretch, lost position at the furlong marker and did not threaten. TEASPOON OF PEPPER showed speed away from the start and assumed command in the early going, set a fast pace into the turn and carved out solid fractions heading to the quarter marker, drifted to the two path nearing the top of the stretch, was overtaken in upper stretch and tired in the final furlong.

ENTRY.NAME: Shelby Gold
ENTRY.OWNER: Lucarelli Racing Corp REV Racing Enterante Frank and Root Rick
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased btwn,2wd turn,3wd into stretch,lost position 1/8,no threat

ENTRY.NAME: Nomi Lackee
ENTRY.COMMENT: bbld/hit gate start,void early speed,chased inside,no factor

Claiming Price $50,0 00 (Races Where Entered For $40,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances) (Cal-Bred Or Cal-Sired Horses That Have Won The Open First Condition Allowance Race In Northern California Must Carry An Additional 2 lbs., Unless Entered For The Optional ClaimingP rice).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TIGER IN MY TANK broke well and took the early lead with GOOD LOVIN in close pursuit, held all at bay through the turn, was challenged by that foe at the five-sixteenths pole, responded then battled on as the two pulled away from the rest, got a nose in front and held. GOOD LOVIN broke well and stalked TIGER IN MY TANK to the turn under a tight old, went to challenge at the five-sixteenths pole then was set down and engaged in a spirited duel to the wire but came up a nose short while drifting in late. CLEVER CLOVER broke out and bumped UNION COACH after the break then got shuffled back, angled to the rail and settled at the rear of the field in the early stages, waited for room through the turn while keeping the rail, got an opening as the field turned for home, put in a good late run, was gaining on the leaders then ran out of race track. TOUGHERTHANTHEREST broke well and was always close up along the rail, ran on well but was outfinished. DADS DREAM broke best but was quickly overtaken, pulled back from a tight spot near the seven-sixteenths marker, raced three wide between horse through the turn, was behind a wall of horses turning for home, then had could not find another gear when needed in the later stages. UNION COACH raced in the middle of the tight pack early, became boxed in through the turn, could not find racing room until the eighth pole then could not improve when clear. AUTISM PUZZLE broke out at the start, then was a bit slow to get going, rushed up into contention before the turn, advanced four wide through the turn while staying clear of any trouble, came under pressure at the top of the stretch, had some trouble changing leads and was outfinished in the late stages.

ENTRY.COMMENT: broke well, always close up, ran on, outfinished

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Gold Rush S. GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 5 1M All Weather Track CR: 84. Stakes Purse 75000. FOR TWO YEAR OLDS. By subscription of $50 each to accompany the nomination or by supplementary nomination of $1,250 at the time of entry which includes all fees. $750 to enter with $75,000 Guaranteed. Weight: 122 lbs. Maidens allowed 3 lbs. Highest earn ings preferred. Closed Wednesday, November 22, 2023 with 10 nominations plus 2 supplementary. A trophy will be presented to the winning owner.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WILD JEWELS broke out a step at the start and bumped SUSHI STICKS, was forwardly placed while a bit keen in the early stages, tracked the modest pace through the backstretch run, was asked for run into the far turn and confronted IMMELMANN approaching the quarter marker, gained command into upper stretch and was confronted by CLASSY CITY at the three-sixteenths marker, battled with that foe to mid-stretch and lost the lead at the furlong marker, came again and battled with CLASSY CITY into the final sixteenth, was carried out in deep stretch when CLASSY CITY drifted, took a narrow advantage in the final strides and held at the finish to determinedly prevail. CLASSY CITY settled in the second flight to begin, tracked the early pace from a two wide path along the first turn, tracked the modest pace while well positioned through the backstretch run, gained ground two wide into the far turn, slipped to the inside and loomed in upper stretch, took command and held a narrow lead at the furlong marker, dueled with WILD JEWELS to the sixteenth-marker, drifted out under firm left handed urging in deep stretch, carried out WILD JEWELS while dueling into the final strides and was bested at the finish, while holding for second. SUSHI STICKS bumped at the start by a neighboring rival and was off a step slowly, settled off of the early pace and raced two wide into the first turn, tracked the moderate pace through the backstretch run and made a mild gain at the half-mile marker, continued to advance two wide along the far turn, angled four wide in upper stretch, was gaining inside of the furlong pole, could not reel in the top pair in deep stretch and was well clear for third. DRUM BUNNY away slowly and spotted the field to begin, was allowed to settle and was guided to the three path into the first turn, was unhurried through the backstretch run, was coaxed along two wide into the second turn, was not able to impact the top three in the stretch drive and passed tiring rivals late. IT AINT OVER tracked the early pace from the inside, gained ground into the backstretch run and was well positioned heading to the half-mile marker, took up leaving the three-furlong pole and lost position approaching the quarter marker, chased into the stretch and did not offer a late rally. IMMELMANN asked for speed away from the start and assumed command in the early going, set a moderate pace into the backstretch run and controlled the pace through modest fractions to the half-mile pole, came under pressure nearing the quarter marker, was overtaken into the stretch, could not keep pace at the furlong grounds and gave way. THERE WAS A STEWARDS' INQUIRY INTO THE RUNNING IN DEEP STRETCH. THE STEWARDS RULED THAT CLASSY CITY DRIFTED OUT INTO THE PATH OF WILD JEWELS IN THE FINAL SIXTEENTH BUT AS WILD JEWELS WAS FIRST PAST THE FINISH, NO ACTION WAS TAKEN.

ENTRY.NAME: Drum Bunny
ENTRY.COMMENT: off slowly,settled 3wd early,2wd 2nd turn,passed tired rivals

ENTRY.NAME: Wild Jewels
ENTRY.OWNER: Williams Larry D and Williams Marianne

ENTRY.NAME: Classy City
ENTRY.OWNER: Eplin Danny A Preiss Daniel and Spencer Arthur

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 6 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 61. Maiden Claiming Purse 14000. FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROCKET RIBBON broke alertly then was taken back to track the solid early pace, raced thee wide into the turn and was asked for run approaching the quarter pole, took command into the stretch, battled with RAMATHORN while drifting out approaching the furlong marker, shook free into the late stages and drew away in deep stretch to be much the best. THIRSTY BABY rated off of the solid early pace, was coaxed along three wide into the turn and gained ground at the quarter marker, swung to the five path into upper stretch and continued his advance at the furlong marker, could not impact the winner in the final sixteenth but was gaining in deep stretch and held clearly in the end for second. WHAT A RELIEF chased the solid early pace between runners, ran in pursuit two wide to the quarter marker and gained ground into the stretch, could not impact the top two in the late stages but ran on in deep stretch and outfinished MOOLA MAN for third. MOOLA MAN chased the solid early pace from the outside, gained ground three wide along the turn, ran evenly to mid-stretch, weakened in the final sixteenth and was outfinished for third. RAMATHORN broke in a bit at the start and crowded RICH SON OF A BUN, was asked to show early speed and assumed command in the opening stages, set a fast pace into the turn then was well rated along the bend, came under pressure at the quarter marker and battled with ROCKET RIBBON into the stretch, could not keep pace with that rival in the final furlong and faded in the late stages. RICH SON OF A BUN crowded leaving the start and was away slowly, spotted the field in the early stages and trailed into the turn, saved ground to the quarter marker, was able to improve position in the stretch but did not factor. ROAD HOUSE chased the solid early pace, came in a bit tight entering the turn and steadied at the three-furlong pole, chased two wide into the stretch and did not threaten. ITS HAPPY HOUR prominent away from the start, tracked the solid early pace between rivals, chased two wide along the turn, lost position into the stretch, was injured approaching the furlong marker, was pulled up and was vanned off.

ENTRY.COMMENT: crowded start,saved ground,improved position stretch,no factor

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 7 1M All Weather Track CR: 87. Claiming Purse 15000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 123 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DE LA LUNA got in a little tight a few strides from the gate, then settled mid-pack through the first turn, stayed out in the clear three to four wide for the backstretch run always traveling well under a rating hold, pulled the rider to the lead passing the quarter pole, responded when set down in the stretch and pulled away from the field to an easy win. LIMITED HEATWAVE raced three wide through the early going and was content to track from the middle of the strung out field to the turn, made a mild forward move while still wide through the far turn, swung out to the five path for the stretch run, kept to task under steady handling and just got up for second. KEEN HEIR broke well and was up on the early pace going into the turn, then backed out of the developing speed duel to a tracking position, was content with that position then looked to improve while racing between horses through the far turn, was set down near the five-sixteenths marker, loomed a threat then had trouble changing leads, could not match the eventual winner but kept to task and was tagged at the wire for the second spot. ALGERIA (IRE) was unhurried from the break and settled towards the back, chased the field to the stretch and made a mild late run to improve position in the final furlong. MOVIETIME raced three wide through the clubhouse turn, settled well behind the field down the backstretch while saving ground along the rail, tried to rally late but did not have a response when needed. RESERVE PROOF was up on the early pace then backed off nearing the six furlong marker while under some restraint, tracked the leading pair to the far turn while racing near the rail and still under a tight hold, waited for room through the far turn, tried to tip out through a narrow opening just past the three-sixteenths pole, was thwarted in that attempt and then was outfinished in the final furlong. WORKDAY was hustled to the front, bumped with HOT JOURNEY near the seven-sixteenths pole, got fanned four wide through that turn, came into the stretch with a short lead but was spent from earlier efforts and gave way readily. HOT JOURNEY took a bump from WORKADAY just before the turn, then raced between a quartet contesting the early lead, traded the lead at various points with that same rival for six furlongs, came under pressure at the top of the stretch and weakened. TALISKER BAY was not asked for speed from the break and settled to the rear of the field through the early stages, was distanced passing the six furlong marker then tried to rally into contention six wide on the turn but could not improve position.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 8 6F All Weather Track CR: 90. Maiden Special Weight Purse 30000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. (If a Cal-Bred Wins This Race, The Owner Will Receive a $10,000 Incentive Award Directly From The California Thoroughbred Breeders' Association.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HATTIE T rated off of the contentious early pace and tracked from the second flight, chased between runners and gained ground two wide along the turn, raced in traffic at the quarter marker and angled four then five wide into the stretch, closed determinedly inside of the furlong pole and wore down rivals into the final sixteenth, surged in deep stretch and was up in the final strides to prevail. VELOCIOUS broke in a step leaving the start and crowded a neighboring rival, was asked for early speed and chased the contentious pace while saving ground into the turn, improved position while in pursuit heading to the quarter marker, found an opening along the rail into upper stretch and loomed approaching the furlong pole, confronted BROADWAY TIGER and battled with that rival into the final sixteenth, took command into deep stretch, fought gamely into the final strides and was tagged on the wire for the win, while holding for second. BROADWAY TIGER broke out a step leaving the start and crowded a neighboring rival, recovered and vied for the early lead with YO BABY, dueled with that runner while carving out solid fractions into the turn, disputed the moderate pace inside of YO BABY approaching the quarter marker, drifted to the two path into upper stretch and held foes at bay to the furlong marker, battled with VELOCIOUS into the final sixteenth, lost the lead to that rival and was outfinished by the top pair in deep stretch, while holding for third in a good effort. CREATIVE QUALITY squeezed leaving the start and was off a bit slowly, recovered and tracked the solid early pace from the second flight, improved position into the turn then came in tight and waited for racing room nearing the top of the lane, angled four wide into upper stretch, finished well in the final furlong and was gaining in deep stretch. YO BABY hustled away from the gate and vied for the early lead, engaged with BROADWAY TIGER and dueled through solid fractions heading into the turn, contested the moderate pace along the bend while outside of BROADWAY TIGER, drifted to the three path into upper stretch and battled to the furlong grounds, could not hold off oncoming rivals in the final sixteenth and weakened. OOPS (GB) ducked out at the start and was off slowly, chased while trailing into the turn, was taken off of the rail and improved position six wide at the quarter marker, swung widest into the stretch, lost ground at the furlong marker and finished evenly. RYE LANE prominent early and tracked the solid pace outside of runners, lost position into the turn and chased five wide to the quarter marker, lacked a response in the stretch and gave way. SPARTA F. C. prominent early, raced close up to the contentious pace while three wide, lost position into the turn and chased four wide to the quarter marker, could not keep pace into the stretch and tired.

(Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $10,000 Or Les s Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WARD 'N JERRY settled mid-pack and well behind the pace to the halfway point, was asked to quicken approaching the three furlong marker, responded with a forward move through the far turn, tipped out through a fortuitous opening at the top of the stretch, ran on well under intermittent urging and was along in time. LAW ABIDING took advantage of trouble to the inside to clear the field from the break and seize the lead and the inside track through the clubhouse turn, went unchallenged on the pace to the stretch, opened up on the field, found another gear, was collared inside the sixteenth pole but held second in a good effort. CANELITO was hustled but outrun to the bend, tracked well behind the top two in the early stages, moved closer through the far turn, loomed a threat passing the quarter pole, could not match strides with the top pair but kept to task and gained third. SUGAR BEETS broke in and bumped with RESPECT THE HUSTLE, had to check briefly then was floated four wide into the first bend, raced three wide near the rear of the field down the backstretch, made good forward progress while saving some ground through the far turn then finished strong under steady handling. TWIRLING DERBY got caught four wide into the first turn then was under some pressure to get closer down the backstretch to no avail, remained wide around the far turn, came into the stretch five wide and produced a mild rally that resulted in some late gain. IL CAPITANO tracked LAW ABIDING from a few lengths back through the early stages, went to challenge approaching the quarter pole, was unable to keep pace and weakened. HOUSE OF LORDS broke out and into RESPECT THE HUSTLE after the break, raced in the middle of the strung out field, went four wide around the far turn and into the stretch and finished evenly. LOOKIN FOR REVENGE broke a step slow then was hustled into traffic, got jostled a bit going into the first turn, then settled near the back, struggled to keep pace on the far turn, came under a ride from the three furlong pole and finished one-paced to the wire. RESPECT THE HUSTLE got squeezed a few jumps from the gate, raced near the rear of the field while under restraint, lost ground on the far turn then tried to rally late but was unable to make an impact.
